        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 0,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1442502809,
        "creation_date": 1442502809,
        "body": "<p>If you invoke <code>InetAddress.getByName()<\/code> with a name that's not really a name, but is an IP address, Java won't perform the DNS lookup.<\/p>\n\n<p>Another option is to use <code>InetAddress.getByAddress()<\/code> like so:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>byte[] numericAddress = new byte[]{127,0,0,1};\nInetAddress.getByAddress(numericAddress); //Will return an InetAddress that points to 127.0.0.1\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
        "answer_id": 32633955,
